wiki.content: "All the Things She Said", English version of "Я сошла с ума", is the first single from t.A.T.u.'s debut English album 200 km/h in the Wrong Lane. The song was a big success based on sales and airplay. It was the first single by a Russian artist to hit the number one in the UK Singles Chart and the Australian number one singles, a position it held for 4 weeks. It is undoubtedly the song that launched t.A.T.u. to stardom. The single has received Platinum and Gold certifications all over the world making its physical and digital sales over 4 million copies.
